<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Deschampsia</i> <i>cespitosa</i> or <i>Festuca</i> <i>rubra</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Agrostis</i> <i>stolonifera</i>, <i>Argentina</i> <i>egedii</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>triangularis</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>lyngbyei</i>, <i>Cirsium</i> <i>vulgare</i>, <i>Distichlis</i> <i>spicata</i>, <i>Erechtites</i> <i>glomeratus</i>, <i>Holcus</i> <i>lanatus</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>corniculatus</i>, <i>Sarcocornia</i> <i>pacifica</i> and <i>Triglochin</i> <i>striata</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal brackish salt marshes (high marshes), alkaline flats. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (2016 national list) recognizes <i>Deschampsia cespitosa </i> as a FACW plant and <i>Festuca rubra </i>as a FAC plant. </div>
</div>

		
